<section class="opening">
<p>This is the web page of the courses
<a href="https://sigarra.up.pt/feup/pt/UCURR_GERAL.FICHA_UC_VIEW?pv_ocorrencia_id=539418"
target="_blank"><em>L.EQ032 &ndash; Physics II</em></a>
and <a href="https://sigarra.up.pt/feup/pt/UCURR_GERAL.FICHA_UC_VIEW?pv_ocorrencia_id=539714"
       target="_blank"><em>L.EA010 &ndash; Physics II</em></a>.</p>
</section>
<section>
<h2>Objectives</h2>
<p>In this course you will learn the foundations of electromagnetism
and the theory of circuits. You will also learn to use instruments for
electric measurements and increase your experience in solving physics
problems. After taking this course you should be able to describe the
main electromagnetic phenomena, analyze direct-current circuits and
do measurements in electric circuits.</p>
</section>
<section>
<h2>Program</h2>
<ol>
<li>Electric force. Electric field. Electrostatic potential.</li>
<li>Electrostatic energy and capacitance.</li>
<li>Electromotive force. Current and resistance. Direct-current circuits.</li>
<li>Magnetic force. Magnetic field. Electromagnetic induction.</li>
<li>Electromagnetic waves.</li>
</ol>
</section>
